Key Terms
Term	Simple definition
Randomized Controlled Trial	Participants are randomly assigned to treatment or control so differences can be attributed to AI.
Treatment Effect	The improvement caused by having AI access.
Skill Compression	AI helps weaker workers more than stronger workers, reducing performance differences.
Task Completion Time	Total time required to finish a task.
Output Quality Assessment	Independent evaluation of the finished work by expert reviewers.

Reading 2
Q1
The “jagged frontier” is the boundary between what tasks are better to use AI or Humans. Because tasks that appear equally difficult for humans may receive completely different levels of AI performance. The boundary isn't predictable from task difficulty alone. That’s why it isn’t smooth.
Q2
Researchers pretested consulting tasks before the experiment to determine which GPT could reliably complete and which required human reasoning beyond the AI’s capabilities. Practitioners usually cannot run formal experiments, so they must rely on experience, pilot testing, and careful validation before deciding where AI belongs in a workflow. 
Q3
Centaur are those where AI is given specific tasks in the style and it doesn’t cross over, while the Cyborg is more fluid and the Human and AI work together continuously. I think for general use a cyborg approach is best, but for trainings and more decision making or research a Centaur approach is best in order to keep a high level of human reasoning involved. 
Q4
They talked about over-reliance on AI and how that led people to not look hard or critically at the work. For an email, this is fine, but for research or decision-making, it could be detrimental. This argument makes sense and is what I would have logically assumed before the data. Again, this highlights that we need to treat “high-stakes” tasks as more Centaur than Cyborg. 

Key Terms
Term	Simple definition
Jagged Technological Frontier	The uneven boundary where AI helps some tasks but harms others.
Centaur Collaboration	Human deliberately assigns different parts of the work to AI and to themselves.
Cyborg Collaboration	Human and AI work together continuously throughout the task.
Over-reliance	Trusting AI too much without sufficient checking or independent reasoning.
Inside-Frontier Task	A task AI can reliably improve.
Outside-Frontier Task	A task where AI performance is unreliable and may reduce human performance.


