Reflection:
The AI produced a well-organized first draft, but it had too much information and things that it didn’t know where completed or not. It focused on things that our meeting wouldn’t care about but it reduced the time spent finding information and it looked at the same meeting from last year to see what I might be missing this year. It did save time looking through two years’ worth of notes and minutes to build a semi-coherent meeting agenda; my own fixes actually made them worse at times.

Disclosure:
I would not disclose AI for meeting agendas. This is just drafting and not publication materials. It is already known by my supervisor that I used AI on them and on the meeting minutes themselves, so it should not be a problem. I am not aware of UA policy that requires it for administrative documents.

